  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What universities does Federal Signal recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Federal Signal Corporation is a global leader in the design, manufacture, and marketing of products and services related to safety, security, and environmental solutions. When recruiting new graduates, Federal Signal typically targets universities that offer strong programs in engineering, business, and related fields. Here's an overview of the types of universities and majors they often seek:\n\n### **Target Universities**\n\nFederal Signal recruits from a diverse range of institutions, including but not limited to:\n\n1. **Large Research Universities:**\n   - **Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)**\n   - **Stanford University**\n   - **University of Michigan**\n   - **Georgia Institute of Technology**\n   - **University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign**\n\n2. **State Universities with Strong Engineering Programs:**\n   - **Purdue University**\n   - **Texas A&M University**\n   - **University of Texas at Austin**\n   - **North Carolina State University**\n   - **Virginia Tech**\n\n3. **Technical Institutes and Specialized Colleges:**\n   - **Rochester Institute of Technology (RIT)**\n   - **California Polytechnic State University (Cal Poly)**\n   - **Carnegie Mellon University**\n\n4. **Business Schools:**\n   - **University of Pennsylvania (Wharton)**\n   - **University of Chicago (Booth)**\n   - **New York University (Stern)**\n\n### **Preferred Majors**\n\nFederal Signal looks for candidates with expertise in areas that align with their business needs. Commonly sought majors include:\n\n1. **Engineering Disciplines:**\n   - **Mechanical Engineering**\n   - **Electrical Engineering**\n   - **Industrial Engineering**\n   - **Civil Engineering**\n   - **Environmental Engineering**\n\n2. **Business and Management:**\n   - **Business Administration**\n   - **Supply Chain Management**\n   - **Marketing**\n   - **Finance**\n\n3. **Information Technology and Computer Science:**\n   - **Computer Science**\n   - **Information Systems**\n   - **Software Engineering**\n\n4. **Other Relevant Fields:**\n   - **Environmental Science**\n   - **Industrial Design**\n   - **Quality Assurance**\n\n### **Recruitment Process and Opportunities**\n\nFederal Signal participates in various campus recruitment events, including career fairs, on-campus interviews, and networking sessions. They also offer internships and co-op programs that can lead to full-time positions upon graduation. To maximize your chances:\n\n- **Attend Career Fairs:** Engage with Federal Signal representatives at your university's career events.\n- **Leverage University Career Centers:** Utilize resume workshops, interview preparation, and job postings.\n- **Connect on Professional Platforms:** Use LinkedIn to connect with Federal Signal recruiters and employees.\n- **Apply Online:** Regularly check the [Federal Signal Careers Page](https://www.federalsignal.com/careers) for job openings and application deadlines.\n\n### **Final Tips**\n\n- **Tailor Your Resume:** Highlight relevant coursework, projects, and internships that align with Federal Signal\u2019s needs.\n- **Prepare for Interviews:** Be ready to discuss how your skills and experiences make you a good fit for the roles you're applying for.\n- **Stay Informed:** Keep up-to-date with Federal Signal\u2019s latest projects and industry trends to demonstrate your interest and knowledge during interactions.\n\nBy targeting universities with strong programs in relevant fields and focusing on the majors that align with Federal Signal\u2019s business objectives, new graduates can position themselves as competitive candidates for roles within the company.",
